Using wtp-sdk-M-1.5.1-200607272136.zip(md5),  WSDDArtifactEdit.getWebServices() seems always return null in the EJB project. i.e. getWsddXmiResource().getContents() is empty.
Hi John, this is blocking the updating of webservices.xml in all Web service scenarios.  So we could not run any Web service creation scenario.  Please let us know if there's any workaround.

The problem really is a fringe case where a file (webservices.xml file) is
created outside the scope of the workspace and the resource was already
existing in memory in the resource set.  The notification was not happening
properly.  This resulted from a performance fix to use edit model caching, and
should be a generic solution to this kind of issue while including the
performance gains of the caching.

The fix to process the added resource event and synch up the resource with what
is on disk. 

This is released for the 080106 WTP 1.5.1 builds.
https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=152493 was opened for the cut and paste problem
